":"1400–1423","1400–Female":"1400–Deceased","1450":"1450","1460":"1460","1490":"1490","after 1423":"after 1423","1459":"1459","1458":"1458","1502":"1502","1425":"1425","1424":"1424","1423":"1423","about 1459":"about 1459","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","1420":"1420","1463":"1463","1508":"1508","19 April 1455":"19 April 1455","1517":"1517","Hedgerley, Buckinghamshire, England":"Hedgerley, Buckinghamshire, England","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","Hedgerley Dean, Buckinghamshire, England":"Hedgerley Dean, Buckinghamshire, England","England":"England","Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":31,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Knyffe was born in 1424, in Buckinghamshire, England, her father, Richard Knyffe - 5th Earl of Salisbury Knyffe of Chaluey, was 25 and her mother, Lettice Smarte, was 25. She married Richard Bulstrode on 19 April 1455, in Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 2 daughters. She lived in Hedgerley, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom in 1458. She died in 1490, in Buckinghamshire, England, at the age of 66."},"et":{"1424–1490":"1424–1490","1425–Female":"1425–Surnud","1420–1502":"1420–1502","1450–Female":"1450–Surnud","1458–1517":"1458–1517","1459–Male":"1459–Surnud","1460–1508":"1460–1508","1463–Male":"1463–Surnud","1400–1423":"1400–1423","1400–Female":"1400–Surnud","1450":"1450","1460":"1460","1490":"1490","after 1423":"pärast 1423","1459":"1459","1458":"1458","1502":"1502","1425":"1425","1424":"1424","1423":"1423","about 1459":"umbes 1459","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","1420":"1420","1463":"1463","1508":"1508","19 April 1455":"19. aprill 1455","1517":"1517","Hedgerley, Buckinghamshire, England":"Hedgerley, Buckinghamshire, England","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","Hedgerley Dean, Buckinghamshire, England":"Hedgerley Dean, Buckinghamshire, England","England":"England","Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1424–1490":"1424–1490","1425–Female":"1425–Kuollut","1420–1502":"1420–1502","1450–Female":"1450–Kuollut","1458–1517":"1458–1517","1459–Male":"1459–Kuollut","1460–1508":"1460–1508","1463–Male":"1463–Kuollut","1400–1423":"1400–1423","1400–Female":"1400–Kuollut","1450":"1450","1460":"1460","1490":"1490","after 1423":"1423 jälkeen","1459":"1459","1458":"1458","1502":"1502","1425":"1425","1424":"1424","1423":"1423","about 1459":"noin 1459","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","1420":"1420","1463":"1463","1508":"1508","19 Apri